BENIN â€“ The Environmental Rights Action/Friends of the Earth (ERA/FoEN), a non-governmental organization has restated the need for proper management of waste in the country. Mr Chima Williams, Executive Director, Environmental Rights Action/Friends of the Earth (ERA/FoEN) made the call during a one day waste management parliament held in Benin, the Edo stay capital. The efforts in that direction, according to him, would assist to reduce unemployment and create jobs for the teeming unemployed army of youths. -Advertisement- Williams noted that the engagement of more personnels in the management of waste is capable of reducing crime and criminality in the country. He called on government and other stakeholders to key into zero waste management practice. Earlier, Former Attorney General and Commissioner of Justice, Dr. Osagie Obayuwana sued for a safe environment for all and the need to create a peoples focused oriented legal framework for an effective waste management system in Edo state. He advised that waste should be properly disposed in order to avoid causing the spread of disease and infections.